article.headline: Houston 78, New Orleans 65
article.story: HOUSTON (AP) -- Lanny Smith scored 30 points and grabbed six rebounds as Houston beat New Orleans 78-65 on Thursday night. Smith sank nine of his 10 free throws and was 8-of-13 from the field. Andrew Owens added 19 points and seven rebounds for the Cougars (6-3). Bo McCalebb led New Orleans (3-5) with 26 points, while Chad Barnes added 10. McCalebb was 11-of-21 from the field and grabbed five rebounds. Houston never trailed, taking a 45-32 lead into halftime.
